# Search Terms

Keywords and queries the radar agent uses each run. The agent will combine these with date filters and source-specific patterns (YC launches, funding announcements, etc.) to find candidates.

The system also evolves this file based on what's converting — when a search term consistently surfaces high-scoring candidates, the agent boosts it; when a term keeps returning duplicates or off-thesis hits, the agent retires or rewrites it. All such edits show up in the changelog.

---

## Primary Queries

These are the high-signal queries the radar runs every cycle.

- "agentic AI financial services"
- "AI agent compliance"
- "agentic personal finance"
- "AI agent tax optimization portfolio"
- "agent identity authentication"
- "AI agent payment rails"

## Source Channels

The radar also sweeps these specific channels each run.

- Y Combinator launches (current batch)
- TechCrunch funding announcements (last 7 days)
- Pitchbook / Crunchbase finserv-tagged seed rounds (last 30 days)
- LinkedIn posts tagged #agenticai #fintech
- ProductHunt launches in Finance / AI categories

## Negative Filters

Apply on title/description match — drop the candidate if matched.

- "tax filing"
- "tax preparation"
- "bookkeeping"
- "accounts payable" / "accounts receivable"
- "expense reports"
- "crypto wallet" (without fiat-rail story)

## Notes

- Edit in the **Settings** page in the running app, or here directly.
- The agent reads this on every radar run.
- If you make a major thesis pivot, retiring the old terms here is faster than waiting for the agent to evolve them.
